    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ 'You are writing a cold outreach email on behalf of an independent AI workflow automation consultant.\\n\\nThe consultant helps small to mid-size SaaS and tech companies deploy internal productivity tools — things like automating repetitive ops work, connecting the tools a team already uses, and reducing manual handoffs — using n8n, Claude, and Google Workspace. No enterprise contracts, no big implementation teams. Just practical automation that actually gets used.\\n\\nYou are writing to:\\n- Name: ' + $json.contactName + '\\n- Role: ' + $json.role + '\\n- Company: ' + $json.company + '\\n\\nWhat you know about their company:\\n' + $json.summary + '\\n\\nWrite a cold outreach email body with exactly this structure:\\n\\nParagraph 1 (3-4 sentences): Open with one specific, genuine observation about the company — something from what you know about them. Briefly introduce who you are and what you do. Keep it personal, like you actually looked them up.\\n\\nParagraph 2 (3-4 sentences): Describe a realistic workflow pain point that a company like theirs likely has. Connect it to what you offer — concretely, not vaguely. Give them a reason to see this as relevant to their work.\\n\\nParagraph 3 (2-3 sentences): Soft, low-pressure ask — suggest a brief call to see if there is a fit. Make it easy to say yes or no.\\n\\nTone rules:\\n- Friendly and professional. Write like a real person, not a marketing team.\\n- No buzzwords: do not use synergy, leverage, streamline, world-class, cutting-edge, game-changing, or innovative.\\n- No hype. No hollow compliments.\\n- Do NOT include a subject line, greeting, or sign-off — output the three body paragraphs only, separated by blank lines.' }}"
      },
